sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Peer A (Uploader)
    participant S as Server (FastAPI + WS)
    participant B as Peer B (Downloader)

    Note over A,B: ── Room Join ──
    A->>S: GET /rooms/{id}  (HTTP)
    S-->>A: room info (has_password?)
    A->>S: WS connect /ws/{room_id}
    S-->>A: { type: "hello", peer_id: "aaa" }
    S-->>A: { type: "user_count", count: 1 }

    B->>S: WS connect /ws/{room_id}
    S-->>B: { type: "hello", peer_id: "bbb" }
    S-->>A: { type: "user_joined" }
    S-->>B: { type: "user_count", count: 2 }

    Note over A,B: ── File Sharing ──
    A->>A: User drops file → stored in localFilesRef (RAM only)
    A->>S: WS: { type: "file_available", file: { id, name, size } }
    S-->>B: WS broadcast: { type: "file_available", file: { id, name, size, peer_id:"aaa" } }
    B->>B: Adds file to UI list (available: true)

    Note over A,B: ── Download (WebRTC handshake via WS relay) ──
    B->>S: WS: { type: "file_request", to:"aaa", file_id, conn_id }
    S-->>A: WS relay: { type: "file_request", from:"bbb", file_id, conn_id }

    A->>A: createRTCPeerConnection + DataChannel
    A->>S: WS: { type: "webrtc_offer", to:"bbb", conn_id, sdp }
    S-->>B: WS relay: { type: "webrtc_offer", from:"aaa", conn_id, sdp }

    B->>B: setRemoteDescription(offer) + createAnswer
    B->>S: WS: { type: "webrtc_answer", to:"aaa", conn_id, sdp }
    S-->>A: WS relay: { type: "webrtc_answer", conn_id, sdp }

    A->>S: WS: { type: "webrtc_ice", to:"bbb", candidate }
    S-->>B: WS relay ICE candidate
    B->>S: WS: { type: "webrtc_ice", to:"aaa", candidate }
    S-->>A: WS relay ICE candidate

    Note over A,B: ── Direct P2P Transfer (no server) ──
    A-->>B: DataChannel: JSON header { name, size, type }
    A-->>B: DataChannel: binary chunks (16 KB each)
    A-->>B: DataChannel: JSON { done: true }
    B->>B: Blob.reassemble → browser download

    Note over A,B: ── Peer Disconnect ──
    A->>S: WS disconnect
    S-->>B: { type: "user_left", peer_id: "aaa" }
    B->>B: marks A's files as available:false → "owner offline"
